      <div class="post-499 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-uncategorized" id="post-499">
        <br><br>
        <div class="entry">
          <p>PKR has entered into administration and is no longer offering gaming services or access to player accounts.</p> 
          <p>If you were an account holder then there is good news. PokerStars, the world’s largest poker site, has stepped up to cover player account liabilities and will be making balances available through the PokerStars platform wherever possible.</p> 
          <p>PokerStars is attempting to contact all former PKR players using registered email addresses. Please check the links below should you require further information.</p>
		  <p>PLEASE NOTE THAT ACCOUNT HOLDERS HAVE UNTIL 28 FEBRUARY 2018 TO CLAIM THEIR BALANCE.</p>
		  <p>PokerStars would appreciate your patience as due diligence is conducted to ensure that the correct funds are credited to the correct players. PokerStars intends to keep all former PKR players well informed by direct email contact, but please check the following two links for immediate information:</p>
          <ul>
            <li><a href="https://www.pokerstarsblog.com/en/blog/corporate_blog/2017/putting-players-first-166975.shtml" target="_blank">Why is PokerStars picking up the bill?</a>*</li> 
            <li>Read the <a href="//www.pstarspromo.com/pkrfaq/" target="_blank">Frequently Asked Questions</a> page</li>
          </ul>
          <p><i>*accessible from most jurisdictions.</i></p>
        </div>
